data.database_description: This database schema is designed to manage and store information about various tourist attractions, including hotels, museums, shops, street markets, royal family sites, and theme parks, within different locations. It captures details such as attraction types, features, opening hours, and visitor reviews. The database also includes tables for visitors, staff, photos, and visits to track interactions and experiences at these attractions. Overall, it serves as a comprehensive system for organizing and retrieving data on tourist sites and their related information.

columns.columnDescription: Code representing the star rating of a hotel.
Description of the star rating code.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Provides descriptions for different star rating codes used in the Hotels table.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each location.
Name of the tourist attraction or location.
Physical address of the tourist attraction or location.
Additional information about the location, such as opening hours and features.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about various tourist attractions, including their types and features.

columns.columnDescription: Unique code for each type of attraction.
Description of the attraction type.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores types of attractions with their descriptions.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each tourist.
Details or name of the tourist.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about tourists visiting various attractions.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each feature.

Description or name of the street market.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each photo.
